BARBERTON – A pedestrian was hit by the driver of a Ford Figo on the R40 towards Stonehenge yesterday morning. ER24’s Kim Habib told Lowvelder they were present on the scene where the man was confirmed dead. Moethi Mmusi, spokesperson for community safety, security and liaison, confirmed the incident, however, he had no further details. ALSO READ: MEC’s motorcade allegedly involved in pedestrian accident